APPEARANCE - light & yellow, light wispy head.
NOSE - grassy hop notes. 
FLAVOR - light & refreshing flavor. Solid lager flavor & balance. Excellent lager the slightest bit of smoke is the last thing I taste with each sip;

]

Pours a clear and effervescent gold, topped by half an inch of white foam. Decent head retention, good webby lacing. Bright and clean malt aroma with quite a bit of tart herbal hop in there too. Second whiff finds some mildly astringent smoke.

Tasty beer, the toasted malt provides a backbone to the earthy spicy hops and the mild (by Schlenkerla standards) smoke profile. Very smooth drinking, nice carbonation levels, medium body. Not overly powerful in the smoke department, but still very satisfying
